data.name: HelpMoveText.Text
data.value:
Clicking on a cell will select that cell.
The arrow keys and TAB allow you to move between cells.
The spreadsheet Wraps, so moving left of A1 will take you to Z1 and vice versa.
Moving up from A1 will take you to A99 and vice versa.

data.name: HelpSetText.Text
data.value:
To set cell contents, move to the cell you wish to change and input the desired contents.
After setting the contents, press enter on the keyboard or hit the enter button to finalize the contents.
If the contents are a formula, the cell will display the value of that formula and the formula box will display the formula.

data.name: HelpOtherText.Text
data.value:
The folder Icon brings up the File Menu
The disk icon will quick save the spreadsheet
Under the file menu: New: opens a new spreadsheet window Close: closes the current window Save As: Opens a dialog box where a name and desitnation can be specified. Open: Opens a dialog box where an existing spreadsheet file can be loaded.
The "Column Information" button returns the sum, count, and average of whatever column the selected cell is on.
The "Row Information" button returns the sum, count, and average of whatever row the selected cell is on.
If any cells, such as variables or formulas, cannot be solved due to incomplete dependencies, they will be left off of the "Information" calculations.
